dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of New Jersey. Atlas Sheet 33 (1905) New Jersey Geological Survey Relief shown by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depths are shown by contours and sounding in feet at low tide. Title is not given. Region covered: vicinity of Barnegat Bay. Original survey 1884, principal features revised 1905. The shore lines of tidal waters, and the triangulation are mainly from the United States Coast and Geodetic Survey. The shore lines of beaches, highways, railroads, and some other details where revised in 1905.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : Geological Survey of New Jersey, 1905.
